         <div type="translation" xml:space="preserve"><head>Translations</head>
            <div type="translation" source="#edd" xml:lang="en"><p>Pota... and Ph..., friends of all, unconquerable throughout their lives.</p></div></div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <head>Commentary</head>
            <p>Lines.4-5, and the wreath suggested a funerary text to Klaffenbach. Although φίλος πᾶσι, φίλος πάντων also seem to occur 
                    in ephebic texts at Ptolemais, a memorial to two men linked in these terms is a little surprising.</p><!-- check -->
         </div>
         
